Jeff Wicks, News24(Netcare 911) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Pretoria - CCTV camera footage of a fatal shooting during a &ldquo;roadblock&rdquo; in Hatfield, Pretoria, on Friday will be a key part of an Independent Police Investigative Directorate (IPID) investigation into the incident.A Tshwane Metro Police officer shot and killed a motorist on Grosvenor Street.News24 earlier reported that a statement released on the SA Police Service's Facebook and Twitter accounts revealed that the victim was a metered taxi driver who apparently tried to run over the officer during a roadblock.The policeman was arrested at the scene.IPID spokesperson Moses Dlamini said CCTV footage of the shooting would be a central aspect of the probe into the shooting.&ldquo;What was in the statement was that there was a roadblock. Already we have witnesses that say there was no roadblock, and the footage that we have in our possession shows no roadblock,&rdquo; Dlamini said.&ldquo;Our investigation is still ongoing and we are not in a position to release anything more. The footage will be a central part of what we are doing.&rdquo;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.